ader, at the forefront of policy-making in Canada’s apparel industry, with commitments to philanthropic efforts that echo his business accomplishments. In My Peerless Story, Segal recounts how he learned business from the collar down and from the ground up, transforming a family-owned business into one that would eventually come to licence labels such as Ralph Lauren, Calvin Klein, and Michael Kors. Sharing anecdotes and personal experiences, Segal describes the history of garment manufacturing in Montreal and his intuitive strategies to leverage growth by improving fabrics, and adapting to innovative changes in the industry, eventually becoming the main inventory source of designer label suits to major department stores. Written from the heart, not as a handbook but rather as the story of a well-suited business career, My Peerless Story nonetheless includes relevant business lessons for the aspiring and inspired.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBusinesspeoplexBiographyxCanada. 0aBusinesspeoplezCanadavBiography. 0aConfectionxHistoirexCanada. 0aGens d'affaires juifsxBiographiesxCanada. 0aGens d'affairesxBiographiesxCanada. 0aJewish businesspeoplexBiographyxCanada. 0aJewish businesspeoplezCanadavBiography. 0aMen's clothing industryxHistoryxCanada. 0aMen's clothing industryzCanadaxHistory. 0aSucc es dans les affairesxCanada. 0aSuccess in business. 0aTailoringxHistoryxCanada. 0aTailoringzCanadaxHistory. 0aV¡etements d'hommexIndustriexHistoirexCanada. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBecker, Hillel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z9783111276199